news.title: Maharashtra pollution board begins survey to inspect RMC plants for compliance
news.para: The survey began on Friday, a few days after residents from Wakad and Thergaon protested against air pollution caused by RMC plants in their area.

news.title: Visakhapatnam's 30-year master plan to be ready soon: Andhra Pradesh minister
news.para: The plan, designed with a 30-year vision, aims to address key urban challenges and foster sustainable development, the minister said.

news.title: Master plan is in place for Coimbatore airport expansion
news.para: ​As per the tender, the estimated cost for the precast boundary wall is Rs29 crore and the work completion period is 456 days. The wall would cover a distance of 16.7 kilometres.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh government vows to resolve land issues in three months
news.para: Sisodia emphasized that joint collectors will directly oversee grievance redressal processes for land issues, ensuring accountability and transparency in all revenue-related activities.

news.title: Madurai civic body collects 80% property tax in FY25
news.para: There is a growing concern over outstanding arrears, which now stand at ₹143 crore, of which ₹83 crore had accumulated over the years. The corporation has recorded 5,885 new property assessments this year, lagging behind Trichy and Coimbatore.

news.title: Mayor tells Kolkata civic body's buildings department DG
news.para: Hakim instructed the director general, Ujwal Sarkar, to monitor the activities of the buildings department officials in the borough.

news.title: Lucknow development body's property registration camp from March 24
news.para: During the first six days, LDA officials and staff will prepare the necessary registration documents. On April 2 and 3, officials from the registration department will be present to complete the registration process at the same venue.

news.title: Get final e-khata within two days, says Bengaluru civic body
news.para: There is no need to visit BBMP offices after application submission. Assistant revenue officers (ARO) and caseworkers will review applications and ensure the final e-khata is issued within the stipulated time frame, he assured.

news.title: Gurugram: DTCP crackdowns on commercial units built on housing plots in DLF areas
news.para: The fire department has been instructed to submit a compliance report before April 19, 2025, detailing the legal actions taken against violators.

news.title: DLF to invest Rs 20,000 crore in medium term to expand its commercial real estate business
news.para: "Significant growth capex being committed for growth," the company said, adding that an incremental capex of around Rs 20,000 crore is planned in the medium term.

news.title: CBI files three FIRs in Rs 9,000-crore Noida Sports City Project 'scam', conducts raids
news.para: ​Acting on the orders of the Allahabad High Court, the agency registered the FIRs against real estate firms Logix Infra Developers Pvt Ltd, Xanadu Estates Pvt Ltd and Lotus Green Constructions Pvt Ltd, their directors and some unnamed officials of Noida Authority, following it up with a search operation, they said.

news.title: Housing ministry approves construction of 3.52 lakh houses in ten states, UTs
news.para: ​​In the statement, the ministry said the approval was given at a meeting of the Central Sanctioning and Monitoring Committee (CSMC) chaired by HUA Secretary Srinivas Katikithala on Thursday.

news.title: Property agents must focus on transparency while facilitating real estate deals: Housing minister
news.para: The minister asked real estate agents to focus on "transparency and trustworthiness", as these are very crucial for the growth in this sector.

news.title: Delhi HC grants bail to Unitech's founder in ED case
news.para: Chandra was arrested by the Enforcement Directorate (ED) in October 2021 in the money laundering case. He was granted interim bail by the high court in 2022 on medical grounds. This was extended from time to time.

news.title: NHB slams home financiers for selling insurance policies with housing loans
news.para: NHB's letter, reviewed by ET, highlights issues identified during supervisory inspections of HFCs, including mis-selling of insurance products along with individual housing loans.

news.title: Three hotels to be developed in Nagpur with an investment of Rs 875 crore
news.para: The three hotel projects will entail a total investment of Rs 875 crore. The MoU for Taj Gateway is separate from the one signed by the Tata Group company Indian Hotels Limited in presence of Chief Minister Devendra Fadnavis in Mumbai last month.

news.title: Odisha HC directs revenue department to address statewide encroachment issue
news.para: Justice S K Panigrahi issued the direction on Thursday while hearing a petition seeking intervention against initiation of eviction proceedings under the Odisha Prevention of Land Encroachment Act on a plot in Bhubaneswar.

news.title: Rajasthan land revenue amendment bill 2025 sent to select committee
news.para: Responding to the debate, Revenue Minister Hemant Meena proposed to send the bill to the Select Committee, which was passed by voice vote.

news.title: Delhi civic body and police launch anti-encroachment drive in Sultanpuri
news.para: Officials stated that the initiative aligns with the MCD's ongoing efforts to restore public spaces, improve urban infrastructure, and maintain civic order.

news.title: No restrictions on land transactions for K-Rail project: Kerala revenue minister
news.para: The minister noted that the K-Rail project has not reached this stage, but any specific cases that arise will be addressed appropriately.
